data.title: 'Jupiter Ascending': 3 points for parents
data.meta_description: Information for parents about the film \
data.text:
Information for parents about the film "Jupiter Ascending."

Violence/gore: A man is shot during a home robbery. A ruthless character kills those who do not do his bidding. Mercenaries and soldiers use futuristic weapons and props to fight each other. A man is jettisoned into space. Humans are probed and tested with needles. Spaceships engage in dogfights around a city. Some blood is seen on wounds. The birth of a child happens in a cargo container.

Nudity/sensuality: A woman comes out of a bath and her body is seen from behind. People are kissing. A man appears naked and is surrounded by women treating him in a sensual way, though nothing is very sexual.

Language: Some uses of profanity

Shawn O'Neill, Deseret News

Shawn O'Neill is the Family Man Movie Reviewer. His reviews are at familymanmovieblog.blogspot.com.
